title: Transgender World Cup swimming races scrapped after no one enters
description: World Cup swimming races designed to accommodate transgender competitors have been abandoned because no one entered.

title: At least 20 dead after coach crashes off overpass near Venice
description: At least 20 people have died in a coach crash near Venice in northern Italy, according to the city's mayor.

title: Tennis player disqualified for smashing ball at umpire's head after losing match point
description: A tennis player has been disqualified from his match after he hit a ball at the umpire, hitting the official in the face.

title: Study reveals how early humans left Africa 84,000 years ago
description: Early humans migrated from Africa 84,000 years ago to populate the rest of the world by following river routes through Jordan - not going via the Red Sea as previously thought, according to a new scientific study.

title: US House Speaker removed from office for first time in history
description: US House Speaker Kevin McCarthy has been removed from office after a historic challenge to his leadership from his own party.

title: 'Natural beauty revolution': Pamela Anderson praised for makeup-free appearance
description: Jamie Lee Curtis has praised Pamela Anderson for showing up to Paris Fashion Week with no makeup on, crediting her with kicking off a "natural beauty revolution".

title: Wrong trousers cost snooker star opening frame
description: A snooker player was docked the opening frame of a match after he turned up in the wrong outfit for the tournament.

title: Onewheel electric skateboards recalled worldwide after deaths
description: All Onewheel self-balancing electric skateboards have been recalled worldwide after at least four deaths and several injuries were reported among people riding them.

title: Fourteen-year-old arrested as three shot dead in Bangkok shopping centre
description: A 14-year-old has been arrested after three people were killed in a shooting at a shopping centre in Thailand.
